translated: Åberg, Ragnar, provincial physician, To-rup, b. 22/12/94 in Skönnerud, Värmland. Son of provincial physician Jacob Gustaf Alarik A. and Anna Sofia Kristina Larsson. Married in 1930 to Harriet Bråkenhielm. Children: Lars Bertil and Inga Margareta, born in 1931. Completed high school in Luleå in 1914, received Bachelor of Medicine degree in Uppsala in 1919, and obtained medical license in Stockholm in 1923. Acting provincial physician in Fränsta district for four months in 1922-1923, assistant physician and acting second assistant physician in Sundsvall hospital surgical department in 1924, practising physician in Ange from 1924 to 1931, railroad physician from 1926 to 1931, in Kiruna from 1931, permanent provincial physician in Kiruna district in the same year, acting second assistant physician in Sandträsk sanatorium for two months in 1933, and provincial physician in Torup district since 1940. In Kiruna, among other positions, served as chairman of the health board and member of the child welfare board and health board in Jukkasjärvi.
